) in lateral view subtrapezoidal, posteriorly strongly produced, with short membranous lobe. Ninth gonocoxite (

Fig. 
22

) broadly foliate, with acute tip. Tenth tergum (

Fig. 
22

) short and slender, with ovoid cercus ventrolaterally.
